---
description: GP-Monorepo code review checklist. Apply when reviewing, auditing, or critiquing code in apps/grampanchayat/ or packages/shadcn/.
globs: apps/grampanchayat/**/*.{tsx,ts},packages/shadcn/**/*.{tsx,ts}
alwaysApply: false
---


Run through each section when reviewing a PR or auditing code.

## Architecture

- [ ] No business logic in route handlers (`app/api/`) — only call `lib/` functions
- [ ] No business logic in `page.tsx` or `layout.tsx`
- [ ] Domain logic lives in `lib/` — not scattered in components
- [ ] Components are UI-only; they receive data, they don't fetch or compute it

## Package Hygiene

- [ ] All imports from `@gp/shadcn` — not `@repo/shadcn` or relative `../../packages`
- [ ] No new packages added without stating why (check `package.json` diff)
- [ ] New shared UI components added to `packages/shadcn/`, not duplicated in the app
- [ ] `package.json` exports updated if new components added to `packages/shadcn/`

## TypeScript

- [ ] No `any` without explanation
- [ ] Props interfaces defined for all components
- [ ] No implicit returns from async functions
- [ ] `typecheck` passes (`pnpm typecheck`)

## Domain Correctness (Namune)

- [ ] Field names match the reconciled spec (`docs/specs/2026-04-18-maharashtra-gp-33-namune-reconciled.md`)
- [ ] Dependencies between registers are respected (e.g. N05 Cash Book is the hub — always updated first)
- [ ] Category grouping matches the vault structure (Budget, Cash, Tax, etc.)
- [ ] Any `[VERIFY]` items from the spec are not assumed to be confirmed

## Tailwind / Styling

- [ ] No hardcoded colour values — use CSS variables
- [ ] No inline `style` objects for layout that Tailwind can handle
- [ ] `@gp/shadcn/globals.css` imported before any custom styles

## Next.js

- [ ] No `use client` on pages that don't need it
- [ ] `transpilePackages` in `next.config.ts` includes `@gp/shadcn`
- [ ] No `console.log` left in production code

## Security

- [ ] No secrets, keys, or credentials in source files
- [ ] `.env.local` never committed
- [ ] User input validated before use

## Git Hygiene

- [ ] No auto-commit or auto-push without explicit user instruction
- [ ] Commit messages describe the "why", not just the "what"
